message.content: We are given that she used a total of 63 cereal bits to create 9 designs, so the average number of cereal bits per design would be $\frac{63}{9} = 7$ bits. It is not possible to say whether Emily used an equal number of cereal bits in each design or not without any additional information. However, we can assume that she may have used more or less than 7 bits for each design depending on the complexity of her designs.
